006package gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.datatype;
007
008import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.util.ObjectUtils;
009
010import java.util.Objects;
011
012import edu.umd.cs.findbugs.annotations.NonNull;
013
014/**
015 * A common base implementation of a custom Java object providing an underlying
016 * implementation of a data type.
017 *
018 * @param <TYPE>
019 *          the bound object type supported by this data type
020 * @param <VALUE>
021 *          the inner value of the data type object
022 */
023public abstract class AbstractCustomJavaDataType<TYPE extends ICustomJavaDataType<TYPE>, VALUE>
024    implements ICustomJavaDataType<TYPE> {
025  @NonNull
026  private final VALUE value;
027
028  /**
029   * Construct a new instance of a custom Java object-based data value.
030   *
031   * @param value
032   *          the bound object that the data type is based on
033   */
034  protected AbstractCustomJavaDataType(@NonNull VALUE value) {
035    this.value = ObjectUtils.requireNonNull(value, "value");
036  }
037
038  /**
039   * Get the bound Java object value.
040   *
041   * @return the bound object
042   */
043  @NonNull
044  public VALUE getValue() {
045    return value;
046  }
047  //
048  // public void setValue(T value) {
049  // this.value = value;
050  // }
051
052  @Override
053  public int hashCode() {
054    return value.hashCode();
055  }
056
057  @Override
058  public boolean equals(Object obj) {
059    return Objects.equals(value, obj);
060  }
061
062  @Override
063  public String toString() {
064    return value.toString();
065  }
066}
